  "body": "{\"query\":\"Next.js production checklist SEO performance accessibility official docs\",\"follow_up_questions\":null,\"answer\":null,\"images\":[],\"results\":[{\"url\":\"https://blog.simplr.sh/posts/next-js-seo-checklist\",\"title\":\"Next.js SEO Checklist | Simplr Blog\",\"content\":\"# Next.js SEO Checklist. ## Next.js SEO Comprehensive Checklist. This checklist is designed to guide you through setting up your Next.js project for optimal SEO performance. Use Next.js 15 or Latest Stable Version:**. + **How:** Ensure your `package.json` has the latest stable version of Next.js. + **Learn More:** Next.js Releases. + **Why:** Next.js’s SSR and SSG are foundational for SEO. - **SSR (`getServerSideProps`):** For content that needs to be updated on each request (dynamic content, personalized pages). + **Learn More:** Data Fetching in Next.js. // app/robots.txt/route.js (Next.js App Router) // app/robots.txt/route.js (Next.js App Router) import { NextResponse } from 'next/server'; import { NextResponse } from 'next/server';  export async function GET() { export async function GET() { const robotsContent = ` const robotsContent = ` User-agent: * User-agent: * Disallow: /staging-area/ Disallow: /staging-area/ Allow: / Allow: /  Sitemap: https://www.yourdomain.com/sitemap.xml Sitemap: https://www.yourdomain.com/sitemap.xml `; `; return new NextResponse(robotsContent, { return new NextResponse(robotsContent, { headers: { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' }, headers: { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' }, }); }); } }. + **Learn More:** robots.txt - Google Search Central. + **Learn More:** Create and submit a sitemap - Google Search Central & next-sitemap. + **Learn More:** Use URL structure - Google Search Central.\",\"score\":0.75616,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://www.lunover.com/blog/nextjs-16-seo-checklist-for-production\",\"title\":\"Next.js 16 SEO Checklist for Production | Lunover\",\"content\":\"Next.js 16 SEO Checklist for Production. A production-ready checklist for Next.js 16 SEO: metadata, canonicals, hreflang, sitemap hygiene, robots rules, schema, and release QA you can automate. The fastest way to lose rankings is to ship one release with inconsistent canonicals, duplicated metadata, or a broken sitemap. This checklist is written for teams building marketing sites and service websites in Next.js 16 (App Router), especially with multiple locales. * Every indexable page has a unique title + description that matches the page intent. * Hreflang points only to real equivalents and includes `x-default x - default`. * Sitemap includes only canonical, indexable URLs and trustworthy `lastmod lastmod`. Do not rely on a single global default for money pages. If your canonical policy is \\\"www + trailing slash + no /en prefix\\\", make sure these never resolve as separate indexable URLs:. Use page-level `noindex noindex` for pages that should never appear in search:. A sitemap is not marketing.\",\"score\":0.74807674,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://www.adeelhere.com/blog/2025-12-09-complete-nextjs-seo-guide-from-zero-to-hero\",\"title\":\"Next.js SEO: Complete Implementation Guide for 2026 | Adeel Imran\",\"content\":\"# Next.js SEO: Complete Implementation Guide for 2026. Cover Image for Next.js SEO: Complete Implementation Guide for 2026. This guide walks you through production-ready Next.js SEO implementation from metadata foundations through performance optimization. It is grounded in the official Next.js Metadata API, Google Search guidance, web.dev Core Web Vitals documentation, and browser platform references. > **Need Next.js SEO implemented professionally?** I help SaaS teams tighten up metadata architecture, structured data, Core Web Vitals, and crawlability in production. If you're short on time, here's what you need to implement for solid Next.js SEO optimization:. * **`sitemap.ts`** and **`robots.ts`** files, which Next.js serves automatically at `/sitemap.xml` and `/robots.txt` via the metadata file conventions. >    <pre><code><span>// app/blog/page.tsx</span> <span>import</span> { buildPageMetadata } <span>from</span> <span>\\\"@/lib/seo\\\"</span>; <span>export</span> <span>const</span> metadata = <span>buildPageMetadata</span>({ <span>title</span>: <span>\\\"Blog\\\"</span>, <span>description</span>: <span>\\\"Insights on web development, TypeScript, React, and building scalable SaaS applications.\\\"</span>, <span>path</span>: <span>\\\"/blog\\\"</span>, <span>keywords</span>: [ <span>\\\"React development insights\\\"</span>, <span>\\\"Next.js best practices\\\"</span>, <span>\\\"TypeScript tips from expert\\\"</span>, <span>\\\"SaaS development blog\\\"</span>, ], }); </code></pre>.\",\"score\":0.73755574,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://www.reddit.com/r/nextjs/comments/195ikpf/nextjs_seo_complete_checklist\",\"title\":\"Next.js SEO Complete Checklist : r/nextjs\",\"content\":\"# Next.js SEO Complete Checklist. I recently found that many Next.js developers struggle to optimize their site SEO performance, especially technical SEO as there are many things to be done. So I wrote this tutorial to show you guys all the necessary things that should be added to your Next.js app to help search engines understand your site better. Read more here: Next.js SEO: The Complete Checklist to Boost Your Site Ranking. Image 7: Thumbnail image: Get Copilot in the apps you know. I believe you can't put the Script tag in Head with the app router. Edit: Also, it's recommended to use the metadata api for all your meta tags with the app router. Edit: I added the guide for App Router also. Image 21 r/nextjs•1y ago    ### What are the first steps to take in a NextJs project? Image 33 r/nextjs•4mo ago    ### What’s one thing you always do in a new Next.js project that isn’t in the official docs?\",\"score\":0.725824,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://nextjs.org/docs/app/guides/production-checklist\",\"title\":\"Guides: Production | Next.js\",\"content\":\"# How to optimize your Next.js application for production. Before taking your Next.js application to production, there are some optimizations and patterns you should consider implementing for the best user experience, performance, and security. This page provides best practices that you can use as a reference when building your application and before going to production, as well as the automatic Next.js optimizations you should be aware of. * **Server Components:** Next.js uses Server Components by default. Server Components run on the server, and don't require JavaScript to render on the client. * **Prerendering:** Next.js prerenders Server and Client Components on the server at build time and caches the rendered result to improve your application's performance. * **Caching:** Next.js caches data requests, the rendered result of Server and Client Components, static assets, and more, to reduce the number of network requests to your server, database, and backend services.\",\"score\":0.6884899,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://github.com/vercel/next.js/discussions/91547\",\"title\":\"How to add automated accessibility testing to your Next.js project · vercel/next.js · Discussion #91547 · GitHub\",\"content\":\"# How to add automated accessibility testing to your Next.js project #91547. | Why accessibility testing matters for Next.js apps Accessibility (a11y) affects both user experience and SEO. Quick scan from terminal (no install) ``` npx accessscore https://your-site.com ```  Runs 16 WCAG 2.1 Level A and AA checks and outputs your score, grade, and top issues. 3. Common Next.js a11y fixes **Document language** (add to `layout.tsx`):  ``` export default function RootLayout({ children }) {   return <html lang=\\\"en\\\">{children}</html>; } ```  **Skip navigation** (first element in body):  ```    Skip to main content  ```  **Image alt text** (use next/image):  ``` import Image from 'next/image'; <Image src={src} alt=\\\"Description of the image\\\" width={300} height={200} /> ```  **Form labels**:  ``` <label htmlFor=\\\"email\\\">Email</label> <input id=\\\"email\\\" type=\\\"email\\\" /> ``` Fun fact I scanned some popular sites:   * **nextjs.org: 100/A** (perfect score!) * **tailwindcss.com: 73/C** (48 issues) * **react.dev: 82/B** (14 issues) * **github.com: 86/B** (9 issues)   Hope this helps!\",\"score\":0.55072874,\"raw_content\":null}],\"response_time\":0.93,\"request_id\":\"cc2b03bf-f251-4fb9-981a-de4233bc9f5e\"}"
